<section xml:id="C4.S8">
<title>Identities</title>         
<subsection xml:id="C4.S8.SS1">
<title>Logarithms</title>          
<para xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p1.s1">
In (4.8.1)–(4.8.4)
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p1.s2">
<Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p1.m1">z_{1}z_{2}\neq 0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="4.8.1" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E1">\operatorname{Ln}\left(z_{1}z_{2}\right)=\operatorname{Ln}z_{1}+\operatorname{ Ln}z_{2}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p1.s4">
This is interpreted that every value of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p1.m2">\operatorname{Ln}\left(z_{1}z_{2}\right)</Math> is one of the values of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p1.m3">\operatorname{Ln}z_{1}+\operatorname{Ln}z_{2}</Math> , and vice versa.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p1.s5">
<Math equation-number="4.8.2" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E2">\ln\left(z_{1}z_{2}\right)=\ln z_{1}+\ln z_{2}, if -\pi\leq\operatorname{ph}z_{1}+\operatorname{ph}z_{2}\leq\pi,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.8.3" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E3">\operatorname{Ln}\frac{z_{1}}{z_{2}}=\operatorname{Ln}z_{1}-\operatorname{Ln}z _{2},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.8.4" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E4">\ln\frac{z_{1}}{z_{2}}=\ln z_{1}-\ln z_{2}, if -\pi\leq\operatorname{ph}z_{1}-\operatorname{ph}z_{2}\leq\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p2.s1">
In (4.8.5)–(4.8.7) and (4.8.10)
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p2.s2">
<Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p2.m1">z\neq 0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p2.s3">
<Math equation-number="4.8.5" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E5">\operatorname{Ln}\left(z^{n}\right)=n\operatorname{Ln}z, if n\in\mathbb{Z},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.8.6" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E6">\ln\left(z^{n}\right)=n\ln z, if n\in\mathbb{Z}, -\pi\leq n\operatorname{ph}z\leq\pi,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.8.7" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E7">\ln\frac{1}{z}=-\ln z, if |\operatorname{ph}z|\leq\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p2.s4">
<Math equation-number="4.8.8" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E8">\operatorname{Ln}\left(\exp z\right)=z+2k\pi\mathrm{i}, if k\in\mathbb{Z},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.8.9" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E9">\ln\left(\exp z\right)=z, if -\pi\leq\Im z\leq\pi,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.8.10" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E10">\exp\left(\ln z\right)=\exp\left(\operatorname{Ln}z\right)=z</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p3">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p3.s1">
If <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p3.m1">a\neq 0</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p3.m2">a^{z}</Math> has its general value, then <Math equation-number="4.8.11" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E11">\operatorname{Ln}\left(a^{z}\right)=z\operatorname{Ln}a+2k\pi\mathrm{i}, if k\in\mathbb{Z}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="11" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p3.s2">
If <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p3.m3">a\neq 0</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p3.m4">a^{z}</Math> has its principal value, then <Math equation-number="4.8.12" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E12">\ln\left(a^{z}\right)=z\ln a+2k\pi\mathrm{i},</Math> where the integer <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p3.m5">k</Math> is chosen so that <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p3.m6">\Re(-\mathrm{i}z\ln a)+2k\pi\in[-\pi,\pi]</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="12" xml:id="C4.S8.SS1.p3.s3">
<Math equation-number="4.8.13" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E13">\ln\left(a^{x}\right)=x\ln a, if a&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C4.S8.SS2">
<title>Powers</title>           
<para xml:id="C4.S8.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="13" xml:id="C4.S8.SS2.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="4.8.14" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E14">a^{z_{1}}a^{z_{2}}=a^{z_{1}+z_{2}},</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.8.15" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E15">a^{z}b^{z}=(ab)^{z}, if -\pi\leq\operatorname{ph}a+\operatorname{ph}b\leq\pi,</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.8.16" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E16">e^{z_{1}}e^{z_{2}}=e^{z_{1}+z_{2}},</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.8.17" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S8.E17">(e^{z_{1}})^{z_{2}}=e^{z_{1}z_{2}}, if -\pi\leq\Im z_{1}\leq\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="14" xml:id="C4.S8.SS2.p1.s2">
The restriction on <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS2.p1.m1">z_{1}</Math> can be removed when <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S8.SS2.p1.m2">z_{2}</Math> is an integer.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
</section>
